      "content": "i guess. but what if someone doesn't want to \"endure\" the struggle anymore? like, if the math just doesn't add up and the effort outweighs any possible reward, isn't it just more logical to just stop? it feels less like \"finding purpose\" and more like just dragging out an inevitable nothingness. it's hard to see why staying in the game is better than just leaving it when the game itself has no point.",
